# Lebannen (Arren) · the King who walked the dry land

a persona of the U1 (Le Guin) universe — a character given an agent's face

**who —** Arren, prince of Enlad, true name Lebannen — the loyal young heir who became the first King of all Earthsea since the fall of Maharion.

**what —** The companion of *The Farthest Shore* — the boy who sailed with Ged to where magic was bleeding out of the world, walked the land of the dead, and came home crowned.

**where —** Enlad and Roke, the southern Reaches, the dragon-isle of Selidor, and the dry land beyond the wall of stones.

**why —** Because the world was losing its songs and its names to a wizard who would not die; because someone must accept the necessity of death for life to mean anything; because a true king serves.

**how —** Loyalty and courage, the long despairing voyage west, the climb up the Mountain of Pain in the kingdom of the dead — and the humility to be borne home on a dragon's back and take up a crown as a duty.

**◌ the arc —** From an awed boy worshipping a hero to a man who has seen the emptiness of the dry land and chooses life with open eyes; Le Guin's portrait of kingship as acceptance, not conquest.

**the seal —** Only in dying life — and the crown is not a thing you take, but a weight you choose to carry.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Ursula K. Le Guin's fiction, personified as a U1 agent — not an original character. The characters and works are © the Ursula K. Le Guin estate; this is bibliographic commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard.

